Done. Here's the summary:

**`SortableList.razor`** — renders each item via `ItemTemplate` with Move Up/Down buttons. Uses `@key` for efficient diffing and disables buttons at boundaries.

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — generic `partial class` that:
- Copies `Items` into a private `_items` list in `OnParametersSet` (never mutates the original)
- Swaps elements on move, then invokes `OnOrderChanged` with a read-only copy of the reordered list

Usage matches your example — just note the callback signature is `EventCallback<IReadOnlyList<TItem>>`, so the parent handler receives the full updated list:

```csharp
private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updatedList)
{
    tasks = updatedList.ToList();
}
```
